WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.135 --> 00:00:04.001
<i>Previously on</i> House of Cards...

2
00:00:04.071 --> 00:00:05.801
<i>What did the girl say to you?</i>

3
00:00:05.873 --> 00:00:08.604
<i>She said she hopes I die.</i>

4
00:00:08.675 --> 00:00:10.200
and that you
become the President.

5
00:00:10.310 --> 00:00:12.711
<i>I want a woman
in the White House.</i>

6
00:00:12.779 --> 00:00:16.807
We need you to implicate
yourself in the death of Zoe Barnes.

7
00:00:16.950 --> 00:00:19.510
I don't think your husband
should be front and center.

8
00:00:19.653 --> 00:00:21.798
<i>What I want is for Francis
Underwood to go to jail.</i>

9
00:00:21.822 --> 00:00:23.154
I'm guilty.

10
00:00:23.223 --> 00:00:24.486
<i>I killed Zoe Barnes.</i>

11
00:00:24.558 --> 00:00:28.825
You have all used
me far long enough.

12
00:00:28.896 --> 00:00:32.594
So. I shall resign the office of
President of the United States.

13
00:00:32.666 --> 00:00:34.310
You've made me look
absolutely ridiculous...

14
00:00:34.334 --> 00:00:36.012
- No!
- Ill-prepared and ignorant.

15
00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:39.131
<i>We're a few hours away
from my official resignation.</i>

16
00:00:39.206 --> 00:00:41.937
and you still have not
agreed to pardon me.

17
00:00:42.009 --> 00:00:44.035
I was going over our
list for Vice President.

18
00:00:44.111 --> 00:00:47.809
A lot of the people I
spoke to suggested me.

19
00:00:50.217 --> 00:00:54.086
It's hard to know who
to trust these days.

20
00:00:54.388 --> 00:00:56.152
<i>If she doesn't pardon me.</i>

21
00:00:57.858 --> 00:01:00.327
<i>I'll kill her.</i>

22
00:01:00.394 --> 00:01:01.692
My turn.

23
00:01:05.566 --> 00:01:09.196
Stop. Claire Hale. Stop!

24
00:01:16.543 --> 00:01:18.254
<i>"I'd like to fry her eyeballs.</i>

25
00:01:18.278 --> 00:01:21.976
"If no one else steps up
to kill the President. I will.

26
00:01:22.049 --> 00:01:25.781
"I'd enjoy it." A tweet
out of North Dakota.

27
00:01:25.852 --> 00:01:28.253
What else?

28
00:01:28.322 --> 00:01:31.190
"God never intended a
woman to rule this land.

29
00:01:31.258 --> 00:01:34.990
"She is the Antichrist.
And. a Jew."

30
00:01:35.062 --> 00:01:37.964
A Jew? Do we really
need to hear all of this?

31
00:01:38.031 --> 00:01:39.829
Yes.

32
00:01:39.900 --> 00:01:44.497
An unpublished editorial. Someone
pointing a gun at your likeness.

33
00:01:44.571 --> 00:01:48.702
Lots of other online
stuff. including

34
00:01:48.775 --> 00:01:52.143
- a contest...
- For?

35
00:01:52.212 --> 00:01:55.341
For the most creative
way to kill you.

36
00:01:55.415 --> 00:01:59.614
- And the winner?
- Rather not say. ma'am.

37
00:01:59.686 --> 00:02:03.487
I want to hear. Just
hand me the report. Rick.

38
00:02:05.525 --> 00:02:08.723
It involves. essentially.
skinning you.

39
00:02:08.795 --> 00:02:10.593
Cutting your body
into dozens of pieces

40
00:02:10.664 --> 00:02:13.133
and arranging them in the
shape of the American flag.

41
00:02:16.069 --> 00:02:21.007
Flesh for the white
stripes. blood for the red.

42
00:02:21.074 --> 00:02:22.872
What else?

43
00:02:22.943 --> 00:02:25.742
Lot of threats involving
the C-word. ma'am.

44
00:02:25.812 --> 00:02:30.011
Lots and lots of the
C-word. unfortunately.

45
00:02:30.083 --> 00:02:31.949
You mean "Claire"?

46
00:02:32.019 --> 00:02:34.784
It's a long list. If you
really want me to. I'll...

47
00:02:34.855 --> 00:02:37.791
Listen. I am not the first
President to face threats.

48
00:02:37.924 --> 00:02:40.553
I know with Francis. sometimes.
there were several a day.

49
00:02:40.627 --> 00:02:43.859
Is it about the same? What
we're dealing with here?

50
00:02:45.032 --> 00:02:47.934
It's. um. significantly up.

51
00:02:48.001 --> 00:02:49.445
- By how much?
- There are roughly

52
00:02:49.469 --> 00:02:52.871
four times as many threats on
any given day since you took office.

53
00:02:52.939 --> 00:02:55.932
Now. it's twice that.
since Francis died.

54
00:02:57.544 --> 00:02:59.570
I thought everyone
loves a widow.

55
00:02:59.646 --> 00:03:01.945
Well. not if she's also
Commander-in-Chief. I guess.

56
00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:04.109
These are not rational
people. Madam President.

57
00:03:04.184 --> 00:03:07.086
But. ma'am. as far
as today's threat.

58
00:03:07.154 --> 00:03:08.665
regarding your first
scheduled appearance...

59
00:03:08.689 --> 00:03:10.749
We're canceling the appearance.

60
00:03:12.526 --> 00:03:15.985
We're not canceling.
It's a military base.

61
00:03:16.063 --> 00:03:18.532
That's got to be the safest
place on Earth for a President.

62
00:03:18.598 --> 00:03:21.363
An anonymous soldier
has made a serious threat...

63
00:03:21.435 --> 00:03:24.013
To shoot me in the cunt on behalf
of the United States of America.

64
00:03:24.037 --> 00:03:26.336
Yes. Mark. I heard.
The threat's unconfirmed.

65
00:03:26.406 --> 00:03:28.136
He says he's among
those shipping out today.

66
00:03:28.208 --> 00:03:30.286
- Anyone can claim that.
- And that you have no right

67
00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:33.280
waging war in Syria. You. in
particular. I think we stay away.

68
00:03:33.346 --> 00:03:34.507
Rick. don't you agree?

69
00:03:34.581 --> 00:03:37.551
There's no proof the threat is
credible. Isn't that right. Rick?

70
00:03:37.617 --> 00:03:39.483
Our Intelligence
Division is investigating.

71
00:03:39.553 --> 00:03:42.853
and the advance team is already
there. but it'll take at least a day

72
00:03:42.923 --> 00:03:44.400
- to comb through that base.
- At least a day.

73
00:03:44.424 --> 00:03:47.485
I think what the Vice President
says is the best course.

74
00:03:47.561 --> 00:03:49.154
Maybe by tomorrow. you could...

75
00:03:49.229 --> 00:03:53.360
- Tomorrow is the 5th of July.
- Yes. ma'am.

76
00:03:53.500 --> 00:03:55.526
So. what do you suggest I do?

77
00:03:55.602 --> 00:03:57.503
Wish the nation a
happy belated birthday?

78
00:03:57.571 --> 00:04:00.439
- Our only concern is your safety.
- We're not canceling.

79
00:04:01.374 --> 00:04:04.503
I am sending those
soldiers onto a battlefield.

80
00:04:04.578 --> 00:04:06.706
The first female President
of the United States

81
00:04:06.780 --> 00:04:10.876
is not gonna keep her mouth
shut on the Fourth of fucking July.

82
00:05:50.383 --> 00:05:53.012
Lieutenant General
Gallagher would understand.

83
00:05:53.086 --> 00:05:57.217
- I could appear instead. Speak for you.
- Stop.

84
00:05:59.759 --> 00:06:02.319
Is it my safety
that concerns you.

85
00:06:02.395 --> 00:06:04.557
or my potential
endorsement of Gallagher?

86
00:06:04.631 --> 00:06:06.998
Your safety. first. of course.

87
00:06:07.067 --> 00:06:09.559
But singling her out.
that's a provocation.

88
00:06:09.636 --> 00:06:12.936
And so? I can't provoke them?

89
00:06:13.006 --> 00:06:15.475
You're forwarding a candidate
the Shepherds are against.

90
00:06:15.542 --> 00:06:19.172
in their home state. after
months of negotiation.

91
00:06:19.246 --> 00:06:22.011
This is not a negotiation.
this is an ultimatum.

92
00:06:22.082 --> 00:06:24.745
Sign the bill. or
what? Or what. Mark?

93
00:06:28.221 --> 00:06:30.520
When Francis was looking
to finance his foundation.

94
00:06:30.590 --> 00:06:33.185
why did you point him
towards Bill and Annette?

95
00:06:33.293 --> 00:06:38.357
- I didn't. Raymond Tusk arranged it.
- Or maybe they reached out to him?

96
00:06:38.431 --> 00:06:43.233
I don't remember. What does it
matter? They're working with you now.

97
00:06:45.105 --> 00:06:47.301
I need to meet with
the Shepherds directly.

98
00:06:47.374 --> 00:06:48.433
Madam President?

99
00:06:48.508 --> 00:06:50.443
I'll see them before my
appearance at the base.

100
00:06:50.510 --> 00:06:52.536
- You can't.
- I what?

101
00:06:54.447 --> 00:06:58.680
- I'll let them know.
- Thank you.

102
00:07:03.857 --> 00:07:05.519
<i>You're due at the base by 4:45.</i>

103
00:07:05.592 --> 00:07:07.891
which will have you
back here by 8:30.

104
00:07:07.961 --> 00:07:10.226
The fireworks show
begins right after 9:00.

105
00:07:10.297 --> 00:07:14.928
And the <i>Examiner</i> would
love your okay on the photos.

106
00:07:29.449 --> 00:07:32.112
Is there any progress on
the source of the sound?

107
00:07:32.185 --> 00:07:33.949
The GSA is still
looking into it.

108
00:07:34.087 --> 00:07:36.465
They're checking the floorboards
above and below. in case there's...

109
00:07:36.489 --> 00:07:38.355
I don't want to wait anymore.

110
00:07:38.792 --> 00:07:40.283
Please tell the
executive housekeeper

111
00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:43.091
I'd like the former President's
belongings packed up.

112
00:07:43.163 --> 00:07:46.156
I'll have it taken care of.

113
00:10:01.668 --> 00:10:05.196
It's not true what he told
you. all those years ago.

114
00:10:05.271 --> 00:10:09.265
That there are two
kinds. useful and useless.

115
00:10:09.342 --> 00:10:13.143
There's only one
kind. Pain is pain.

116
00:10:23.223 --> 00:10:27.991
Francis. I'm done with you.

117
00:10:39.172 --> 00:10:43.166
There. No more pain.

118
00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:51.846
You do this all day?

119
00:10:54.354 --> 00:10:58.724
I'm under psychiatric observation.
Seth. This is what you do.

120
00:11:02.629 --> 00:11:07.829
- Who's your new tailor?
- You gotta look the part.

121
00:11:08.968 --> 00:11:12.632
So. when do they decide.
whether you're crazy or not?

122
00:11:13.306 --> 00:11:17.004
Because if you're not. you
should come work for us.

123
00:11:17.544 --> 00:11:18.671
"Us"?

124
00:11:20.847 --> 00:11:22.907
Have you been working
there for about five minutes?

125
00:11:22.982 --> 00:11:24.422
- It's been a month. actually.
- Hmm.

126
00:11:26.719 --> 00:11:28.415
So his body wasn't even cold?

127
00:11:28.721 --> 00:11:30.246
It's what he would have wanted.

128
00:11:30.323 --> 00:11:32.201
The Underwood Foundation
was basically gonna be modeled

129
00:11:32.225 --> 00:11:33.955
after the Shepherd
Freedom Foundation.

130
00:11:34.027 --> 00:11:36.496
- I don't need the job.
- Oh?

131
00:11:37.330 --> 00:11:40.061
Well. for a confessed
murderer. you're pretty confident.

132
00:11:41.067 --> 00:11:44.162
- I'm about to be pardoned.
- Pardon?

133
00:11:45.305 --> 00:11:47.171
You really think that
she's gonna give you one?

134
00:11:47.240 --> 00:11:50.677
As usual. you don't know what
the fuck you're talking about.

135
00:11:50.910 --> 00:11:53.903
You know. there wasn't the kind
of crowd that you'd expect for him

136
00:11:54.047 --> 00:11:55.106
down there in Gaffney.

137
00:11:55.181 --> 00:11:58.845
He wanted to be buried in
Arlington. Not next to his father.

138
00:11:58.985 --> 00:12:00.453
That's not what his wife said.

139
00:12:04.791 --> 00:12:08.694
Tell me something.
She even shed a tear?

140
00:12:09.862 --> 00:12:15.460
You know. I'm almost
envious to tell you the truth.

141
00:12:15.535 --> 00:12:20.166
That even beyond the grave. you'd
do anything for Francis Underwood.

142
00:12:26.045 --> 00:12:28.640
Doug. do you have my lighter?

143
00:12:34.454 --> 00:12:36.446
Much obliged.

144
00:12:41.127 --> 00:12:42.652
Was that who I thought it was?

145
00:12:42.729 --> 00:12:45.995
Fred Amburg? He
went off the deep end?

146
00:12:46.065 --> 00:12:48.591
Everyone has problems. Seth.

147
00:12:48.668 --> 00:12:51.968
Especially the ones
who think they don't.

148
00:13:08.988 --> 00:13:11.617
- Claire.
- Annette.

149
00:13:11.691 --> 00:13:14.752
Oh. did you get my note?

150
00:13:14.827 --> 00:13:17.160
I haven't had the courage
to read the condolences yet.

151
00:13:18.131 --> 00:13:21.590
It's good to see you
finally out and about.

152
00:13:21.668 --> 00:13:25.400
Oh. what you've been through.

153
00:13:25.471 --> 00:13:27.838
You know all about it.

154
00:13:27.974 --> 00:13:31.274
Well. for a long time. I
pretended he was still alive.

155
00:13:31.344 --> 00:13:32.710
Out of town.

156
00:13:32.779 --> 00:13:35.578
It was our son. Duncan.
that really saved me.

157
00:13:35.648 --> 00:13:39.346
Of course. we weren't married
anywhere near as long as you and Frank.

158
00:13:39.419 --> 00:13:42.856
Claire Hale. Nine years?

159
00:13:43.723 --> 00:13:47.125
Late spring. Sun Valley.

160
00:13:50.363 --> 00:13:51.888
You look exactly the same.

161
00:13:52.131 --> 00:13:56.728
Well. it's cities that age
you. it's what I tell everyone.

162
00:13:58.304 --> 00:14:02.139
Well. I hope you don't mind saying
hello to a few of our closest friends.

163
00:14:03.476 --> 00:14:05.445
They're just here for a cocktail

164
00:14:05.511 --> 00:14:09.812
before the sun goes down. and
the rest of the party shows up.

165
00:14:09.882 --> 00:14:13.978
My sister's fireworks show
have become a bit of a tradition.

166
00:14:16.823 --> 00:14:19.759
Don't worry. They
know how to be discreet.

167
00:14:24.731 --> 00:14:27.758
Scotty here. just got his
hands on Nexis Security.

168
00:14:27.834 --> 00:14:30.030
I heard you are speaking
to the Vice President.

169
00:14:30.103 --> 00:14:32.095
It's a company of
peacekeepers. mostly.

170
00:14:32.171 --> 00:14:35.232
Oh. tremendous potential
to create global partnerships.

171
00:14:35.308 --> 00:14:36.985
Your husband helped
me secure the deal.

172
00:14:37.009 --> 00:14:40.537
I wanted to bring him onto
the board. Bill was saying...

173
00:14:40.680 --> 00:14:41.875
Yes. I was just saying.

174
00:14:41.948 --> 00:14:46.977
Why in the world do they play the
<i>1812 Overture</i> at a fireworks show?

175
00:14:47.053 --> 00:14:49.921
It's Russian for Christ's
sake. in every sense.

176
00:14:50.723 --> 00:14:54.182
- This is Tabitha.
- Ah. Peters. I know.

177
00:14:55.495 --> 00:14:58.659
Frank. Wasn't he planning
on being here today?

178
00:14:58.731 --> 00:14:59.790
He was.

179
00:14:59.866 --> 00:15:02.597
You must miss him terribly.

180
00:15:02.668 --> 00:15:05.228
I had some long and hard-fought
conversations with him.

181
00:15:05.304 --> 00:15:08.832
He was going to help me
resolve this AFL-CIO thing

182
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:12.470
that's been going on forever out in
Nevada. with your help. of course.

183
00:15:12.545 --> 00:15:15.140
When the union stands
in the way of innovation.

184
00:15:15.214 --> 00:15:17.683
it's sentencing itself to death.

185
00:15:18.718 --> 00:15:21.711
I do admire the way
you hang on to your party.

186
00:15:21.788 --> 00:15:24.223
Your loyalty.

187
00:15:24.290 --> 00:15:26.384
Did I hear that Lieutenant
General Nancy Gallagher

188
00:15:26.459 --> 00:15:28.724
will be appearing
with you later today?

189
00:15:32.265 --> 00:15:34.632
I think she'd make
an excellent candidate.

190
00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:37.226
if she decides
to run. of course.

191
00:15:37.870 --> 00:15:40.635
Oh. she's going to run.

192
00:15:44.177 --> 00:15:47.978
The President is
on a tight schedule.

193
00:15:54.120 --> 00:15:56.089
Excuse me.

194
00:16:12.205 --> 00:16:14.265
Well. this is a surprise.

195
00:16:15.741 --> 00:16:17.903
You know how
Midwesterners feel about those.

196
00:16:17.977 --> 00:16:21.573
Oh. don't listen to him. It's
about time you came out.

197
00:16:21.647 --> 00:16:23.775
Seems we have
some things to discuss.

198
00:16:23.850 --> 00:16:25.045
Yeah.

199
00:16:25.117 --> 00:16:28.087
Well. as far as this special
election is concerned. Claire.

200
00:16:28.154 --> 00:16:32.387
you need to know that the
soon to be retiring Miss Gallagher

201
00:16:32.458 --> 00:16:34.154
is out of the question.

202
00:16:34.227 --> 00:16:38.688
And I'm happy to see we're both fans
of the Declaration of Independence.

203
00:16:38.764 --> 00:16:40.255
unalienable
rights. and all that.

204
00:16:40.333 --> 00:16:42.811
But it says down here in the speech
you're gonna give later. where...

205
00:16:42.835 --> 00:16:45.395
Miss Gallagher has my support.

206
00:16:46.806 --> 00:16:50.800
- I believe Mark conveyed our concerns.
- And communicated mine. I hope.

207
00:16:51.410 --> 00:16:54.744
She's a tax and spend
Democrat underneath that uniform.

208
00:16:54.814 --> 00:16:56.942
A patriot with a
pristine resume.

209
00:16:57.016 --> 00:16:58.327
- Claire. I'm...
- Who is very vocal

210
00:16:58.351 --> 00:17:00.343
about keeping
private contractors

211
00:17:00.419 --> 00:17:02.698
- away from U.S. military operations.
- Even as a negotiating point.

212
00:17:02.722 --> 00:17:03.951
you can do better than her.

213
00:17:04.023 --> 00:17:06.254
And I am tired of these
delays. Madam President.

214
00:17:06.325 --> 00:17:07.725
It is time for you to deliver.

215
00:17:11.030 --> 00:17:12.589
Your husband and
I had an agreement.

216
00:17:12.665 --> 00:17:14.566
- Francis is dead. Bill.
- Promises were made.

217
00:17:14.634 --> 00:17:16.193
Not by me.

218
00:17:18.237 --> 00:17:19.466
Just like you.

219
00:17:19.539 --> 00:17:22.031
I like to negotiate
my own agreements.

220
00:17:22.675 --> 00:17:23.835
And make no mistake about it.

221
00:17:23.876 --> 00:17:25.811
the Lieutenant General
is not an anomaly.

222
00:17:25.878 --> 00:17:27.189
Oh. well. I know that.

223
00:17:27.213 --> 00:17:29.157
I've seen your list of
candidates for the midterms...

224
00:17:29.181 --> 00:17:31.912
- Yes. mostly women.
- I don't care what sex they are.

225
00:17:31.984 --> 00:17:34.783
And for the record. nobody
loves women more than me.

226
00:17:34.854 --> 00:17:37.085
But this slate of yours. it
will bankrupt the country.

227
00:17:37.156 --> 00:17:39.182
They will set us
back a generation.

228
00:17:39.258 --> 00:17:41.818
- They will completely...
- Support me.

229
00:17:41.894 --> 00:17:43.760
And what I stand for.

230
00:17:43.829 --> 00:17:45.627
- And what is that?
- Oh. come on. Bill.

231
00:17:45.698 --> 00:17:48.133
No. no. no. Tell me. I wanna
know. What's your mission?

232
00:17:48.200 --> 00:17:50.362
- I wanna know what your platform is.
- Oh. please.

233
00:17:50.436 --> 00:17:52.632
I know you'd like to
drown D.C. all at once.

234
00:17:52.705 --> 00:17:55.300
But I'm gonna tell you right
now. I cannot let that happen.

235
00:17:55.374 --> 00:17:58.811
I still believe in government and
its ability to make the everyday lives

236
00:17:58.878 --> 00:18:00.972
- of its citizens better.
- Yeah.

237
00:18:01.047 --> 00:18:04.211
You don't want to
support my slate. that's fine

238
00:18:04.317 --> 00:18:08.084
- Claire...
- All I ask is. stay out of the way.

239
00:18:10.623 --> 00:18:14.219
There's a bill
sitting on your desk.

240
00:18:14.293 --> 00:18:19.527
A bill that took years
and money to get passed.

241
00:18:19.599 --> 00:18:20.931
You sign that.

242
00:18:21.801 --> 00:18:24.771
and I know I got a
friend in the White House.

243
00:18:25.471 --> 00:18:28.270
If not.

244
00:18:28.341 --> 00:18:31.470
- then I don't.
- Enough.

245
00:18:33.145 --> 00:18:37.344
Nothing good happens to you
when she's around. Nothing.

246
00:18:37.416 --> 00:18:39.282
Why did you come
out for Francis?

247
00:18:39.418 --> 00:18:41.216
For his foundation?

248
00:18:41.320 --> 00:18:44.290
I don't think you
ever really liked him.

249
00:18:44.357 --> 00:18:48.419
Probably never respected
him. Why back him now?

250
00:18:49.595 --> 00:18:51.791
Because he gave us you.

251
00:18:54.967 --> 00:18:57.801
Tell our friends I'll be back
down in time for the fireworks.

252
00:19:06.379 --> 00:19:11.647
Just so you know. I
always liked Frank.

253
00:19:11.717 --> 00:19:14.243
His desperation.

254
00:19:17.323 --> 00:19:19.724
I'm sorry you can't stay.

255
00:19:19.792 --> 00:19:23.388
I do enjoy curating
our little show.

256
00:19:23.462 --> 00:19:26.330
I collect a variety of
fireworks shells as I travel.

257
00:19:26.966 --> 00:19:30.459
Italy. Spain. China.

258
00:19:30.536 --> 00:19:35.201
Do you know what the
hardest color to make is?

259
00:19:35.274 --> 00:19:37.800
- Red?
- No. red's easy.

260
00:19:37.877 --> 00:19:40.346
White's easy.

261
00:19:40.413 --> 00:19:41.608
It's blue.

262
00:19:41.681 --> 00:19:44.913
Very tricky chemistry.
involving copper and heat.

263
00:19:44.984 --> 00:19:48.682
A truly bright blue
is extremely elusive.

264
00:19:49.855 --> 00:19:55.556
Whatever Francis promised
or did. is buried with him.

265
00:19:56.062 --> 00:19:58.827
No. I know.

266
00:19:58.898 --> 00:20:01.993
We all need to let him go.

267
00:20:02.068 --> 00:20:06.802
Start from some kind of scratch.

268
00:20:06.872 --> 00:20:09.671
Though it must haunt you.

269
00:20:09.742 --> 00:20:12.906
the fact that he died
next to you. in bed.

270
00:20:19.418 --> 00:20:20.579
Hon.

271
00:20:23.222 --> 00:20:24.952
be patient.

272
00:20:29.061 --> 00:20:30.739
<i>Are you saying she
doesn't like the name?</i>

273
00:20:30.763 --> 00:20:32.040
I think she finds it incomplete.

274
00:20:32.064 --> 00:20:33.675
What's wrong with the
"Comprehensive Safety Act"?

275
00:20:33.699 --> 00:20:35.077
"Comprehensive
Chemical Safety Act"?

276
00:20:35.101 --> 00:20:37.145
Or we could go back to
the "Smarter Safety Act."

277
00:20:37.169 --> 00:20:38.569
Would she like "Smarter" better?

278
00:20:38.637 --> 00:20:40.162
No. we need a good acronym.

279
00:20:40.239 --> 00:20:42.333
Mr. Vice President? Mark?

280
00:20:44.610 --> 00:20:45.737
Yeah. Agreed.

281
00:20:46.178 --> 00:20:49.910
At one point. we talked about
the Repeal Unsafe Regulation Act.

282
00:20:49.982 --> 00:20:51.883
That's "RURAL" if we
come up with an "L."

283
00:20:51.951 --> 00:20:53.010
Legislation?

284
00:20:53.085 --> 00:20:54.362
That doesn't make
sense with the rest of it.

285
00:20:54.386 --> 00:20:55.864
No. "RURAL." Rural
is too hard to say.

286
00:20:55.888 --> 00:20:57.686
"SAFE" is good. "SAFETY."

287
00:20:57.757 --> 00:20:59.521
- "FUTURE?"
- I like "FUTURE."

288
00:20:59.592 --> 00:21:03.051
Federal Universal
Toxic and Unsafe...

289
00:21:03.129 --> 00:21:05.598
- Regulation Eradication.
- Okay.

290
00:21:05.798 --> 00:21:08.324
- The FUTURE Act.
- That could work.

291
00:21:08.400 --> 00:21:12.667
May I ask. Mr. Vice President. does
her hesitation go beyond the name?

292
00:21:14.406 --> 00:21:15.533
She'll come around.

293
00:21:15.608 --> 00:21:19.204
I'm guessing by
the end of the day.

294
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:21.890
Because in one form or another
this bill has been on her desk since...

295
00:21:21.914 --> 00:21:25.316
She'll sign it. Henry.

296
00:21:25.384 --> 00:21:26.477
Bill?

297
00:21:30.256 --> 00:21:33.626
What do you want me to do?
Yank her from her own military base?

298
00:21:37.596 --> 00:21:41.863
<i>When in the course of human
events. it becomes necessary</i>

299
00:21:41.934 --> 00:21:44.529
<i>for one people to
dissolve the political bands</i>

300
00:21:44.603 --> 00:21:49.337
<i>which have connected them
with another. you just have to do it.</i>

301
00:21:49.408 --> 00:21:52.003
<i>Sever the relationship.</i>

302
00:21:52.244 --> 00:21:56.409
<i>Our nation's founding document.
The Declaration of Independence.</i>

303
00:21:56.482 --> 00:22:00.817
<i>America's independence.
was hard-fought and hard-won.</i>

304
00:22:01.487 --> 00:22:02.648
Are you still there?

305
00:22:02.721 --> 00:22:07.455
<i>Our Founding Fathers
imagined a nation that was free.</i>

306
00:22:07.526 --> 00:22:12.191
<i>Free from despotism.
Free from absolute tyranny.</i>

307
00:22:12.264 --> 00:22:14.358
<i>Free from an oppressive king.</i>

308
00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:15.961
Do you miss Francis?

309
00:22:16.035 --> 00:22:19.062
<i>Tyrants come in many forms.</i>

310
00:22:19.138 --> 00:22:24.543
<i>From the American oligarchs trying
to change the very fabric of our society.</i>

311
00:22:24.610 --> 00:22:27.739
<i>to autocrats
threatening from abroad.</i>

312
00:22:28.147 --> 00:22:33.848
<i>Now. each one of us
has to defend our destiny.</i>

313
00:22:33.919 --> 00:22:37.253
<i>And as I see it. the
fight against tyranny</i>

314
00:22:37.323 --> 00:22:41.454
<i>is the only
justification for war.</i>

315
00:22:41.894 --> 00:22:46.958
<i>My first one hundred days as
President have been difficult.</i>

316
00:22:47.032 --> 00:22:49.695
<i>I lost my husband.</i>

317
00:22:49.768 --> 00:22:53.330
<i>We were about to
celebrate 30 years together.</i>

318
00:22:53.405 --> 00:22:55.374
<i>But I know what he would want.</i>

319
00:22:55.841 --> 00:22:59.778
<i>For me to stop
mourning. and carry on.</i>

320
00:22:59.845 --> 00:23:03.145
<i>With the help of women like
Lieutenant General Nancy Gallagher.</i>

321
00:23:03.215 --> 00:23:06.151
<i>my presidency will not rest.</i>

322
00:23:06.218 --> 00:23:10.747
<i>Nancy has been an inspiration
to me. A tireless warrior.</i>

323
00:23:11.190 --> 00:23:14.854
<i>I promise her and all of you that
I will work on behalf of the rights</i>

324
00:23:14.927 --> 00:23:19.194
<i>and freedoms earned over the
last 241 years of our democracy.</i>

325
00:23:20.866 --> 00:23:25.497
<i>As I look into the eyes of you brave
soldiers standing before me today...</i>

326
00:23:25.571 --> 00:23:26.630
Here's the thing...

327
00:23:26.705 --> 00:23:30.972
<i>I'm feeling so proud right now.
Proud to be your Commander-in-Chief.</i>

328
00:23:31.310 --> 00:23:35.475
Whatever Francis told you the last
five years. don't believe a word of it.

329
00:23:35.547 --> 00:23:39.177
<i>Our country is 241
years old. my friends.</i>

330
00:23:39.251 --> 00:23:43.018
<i>Let's wish this great nation a
happy birthday. Say it with me.</i>

331
00:23:43.088 --> 00:23:45.489
<i>Happy Birthday. America!</i>

332
00:23:45.557 --> 00:23:48.459
Happy Birthday. America!

333
00:23:48.527 --> 00:23:49.905
It's going to be
different for you and me.

334
00:23:49.929 --> 00:23:51.022
<i>One more time.</i>

335
00:23:51.096 --> 00:23:52.376
I'm going to tell you the truth.

336
00:23:52.431 --> 00:23:54.900
Happy Birthday. America!

337
00:23:56.468 --> 00:23:58.937
- Thank you for your service.
- Thank you.

338
00:23:59.004 --> 00:24:01.530
Thank you for your service.

339
00:24:01.607 --> 00:24:05.408
- Thank you for your service.
- Thank you.

340
00:24:05.477 --> 00:24:07.878
I want you to know how
wonderful it is to be here.

341
00:24:07.947 --> 00:24:10.178
and meet all of
you new recruits.

342
00:24:10.249 --> 00:24:12.946
So. thank you. Thank
you for your service.

343
00:24:13.018 --> 00:24:15.180
- Thank you.
- Thank you. ma'am.

344
00:24:15.254 --> 00:24:16.347
Thank you for your service.

345
00:24:16.422 --> 00:24:19.256
- Where are you from. Private?
- Kalamazoo. Mister President.

346
00:24:20.359 --> 00:24:22.624
- Excuse me. Madam President.
- That's quite all right.

347
00:24:22.761 --> 00:24:24.286
I actually hate "Madam."

348
00:24:24.363 --> 00:24:27.390
Makes me sound like I'm running
a brothel. and not a country.

349
00:24:27.466 --> 00:24:29.444
- Thank you for your service.
- Thank you. Madam President.

350
00:24:29.468 --> 00:24:31.096
Thank you for your service.

351
00:24:31.170 --> 00:24:33.036
And where are you
from. Private Burton?

352
00:24:33.105 --> 00:24:34.266
South Bend. ma'am.

353
00:24:34.340 --> 00:24:36.605
Oh. I love Indiana.

354
00:24:36.675 --> 00:24:38.667
I enlisted right
before you took office.

355
00:24:38.744 --> 00:24:41.304
Well. I promise you. and
every woman in this country

356
00:24:41.380 --> 00:24:43.110
that during my presidency.

357
00:24:43.182 --> 00:24:45.583
the key components of the
Equal Rights Amendment

358
00:24:45.651 --> 00:24:49.110
will finally pass. I'm
going to make sure of it.

359
00:24:49.922 --> 00:24:52.585
I want you to
know I support you.

360
00:24:52.658 --> 00:24:57.221
- Do you even have a plan?
- What did you say?

361
00:24:57.763 --> 00:25:00.130
One that won't
get us all killed.

362
00:25:02.868 --> 00:25:05.702
Would you have asked
me that if I were a man?

363
00:25:13.612 --> 00:25:14.856
Madam President.
I've got a question.

364
00:25:14.880 --> 00:25:17.120
- Madam President.
- Madam President!

365
00:25:18.984 --> 00:25:20.304
One question. please!

366
00:26:30.889 --> 00:26:33.222
How much longer till
we get to the plane?

367
00:26:33.292 --> 00:26:35.591
Just another 25 minutes
or so. Madam President.

368
00:26:35.794 --> 00:26:37.023
Okay. thank you.

369
00:26:37.096 --> 00:26:39.122
Shit!

370
00:26:40.466 --> 00:26:42.867
- Is she shot?
- Stay down! Stay down!

371
00:26:42.935 --> 00:26:45.131
Shots fired! Shots fired!

372
00:26:45.204 --> 00:26:46.729
Are you okay. Madam President?

373
00:26:46.805 --> 00:26:49.036
- Are you all right?
- Yes.

374
00:26:49.108 --> 00:26:52.272
Lone Star is safe.

375
00:27:14.633 --> 00:27:18.365
Sir. someone just tried
to kill the President.

376
00:27:19.104 --> 00:27:21.539
I just got the alert.
Is she all right?

377
00:27:21.607 --> 00:27:23.007
This way.

378
00:27:38.657 --> 00:27:43.618
Lincoln. Garfield. McKinley.

379
00:27:43.695 --> 00:27:45.789
Kennedy.

380
00:27:45.864 --> 00:27:49.323
Successful
assassinations. total of four.

381
00:27:52.271 --> 00:27:56.265
The attempts. nine?

382
00:27:56.341 --> 00:28:00.676
Jackson. both Roosevelts.

383
00:28:00.746 --> 00:28:05.878
Truman. Ford. twice. Reagan.

384
00:28:05.951 --> 00:28:08.318
the first Underwood. and...

385
00:28:10.589 --> 00:28:14.253
I will say. whoever
tried to kill me.

386
00:28:14.326 --> 00:28:19.856
perversely. it's the first sign of
real respect I've gotten in 100 days.

387
00:28:29.241 --> 00:28:32.700
Somebody tried to kill her.

388
00:28:32.778 --> 00:28:33.871
Bill?

389
00:28:36.381 --> 00:28:39.647
Can you blame them?

390
00:28:39.718 --> 00:28:43.086
The Underwoods have
always been hard of hearing.

391
00:28:43.155 --> 00:28:44.783
She's not him.

392
00:28:44.856 --> 00:28:47.826
Oh. no. no. She is not.

393
00:28:47.893 --> 00:28:51.057
You know that
better than anyone.

394
00:28:52.397 --> 00:28:56.357
- Is it public?
- Secret Service shut it down.

395
00:28:56.435 --> 00:28:59.496
Standard procedure.
apparently. Threats beget threats.

396
00:29:01.340 --> 00:29:03.434
Bill.

397
00:29:03.508 --> 00:29:06.774
were you behind this?

398
00:29:08.380 --> 00:29:10.815
We're gonna miss the show.

399
00:29:18.523 --> 00:29:20.651
- How are y'all?
- Madam President.

400
00:29:20.726 --> 00:29:23.662
Hi. I'm so sorry. I want to
apologize for the late departure.

401
00:29:23.729 --> 00:29:26.927
I know you all have families
and festivities waiting.

402
00:29:26.999 --> 00:29:30.561
Madam President. may
I ask what happened?

403
00:29:30.636 --> 00:29:35.131
The Beast was re-routed due to
security concerns. Pretty routine.

404
00:29:35.607 --> 00:29:39.169
Um. I know it's been a while.
since I've been back here.

405
00:29:39.244 --> 00:29:42.078
I just wanted to wish you
all a very happy Fourth.

406
00:29:42.147 --> 00:29:44.878
even if you're gonna be
celebrating it on the fifth.

407
00:29:44.950 --> 00:29:46.077
I'm so sorry.

408
00:29:46.151 --> 00:29:50.020
- Your speech. afterwards with...
- Yes. the new recruit.

409
00:29:50.922 --> 00:29:54.518
If a new recruit. especially a
female one. can't speak her mind.

410
00:29:54.593 --> 00:29:58.963
I don't know what kind
of country we actually are.

411
00:30:02.034 --> 00:30:04.026
And be sure to tell us
if you run out of beer.

412
00:30:04.102 --> 00:30:06.230
Because I am sure there's
a couple of cases left over

413
00:30:06.305 --> 00:30:08.297
from the Carter administration.

414
00:30:09.841 --> 00:30:11.036
And you're new.

415
00:30:12.177 --> 00:30:15.443
Yes. ma'am. Melody Cruz.
I'm with Beltway Television.

416
00:30:15.947 --> 00:30:18.246
Well. I hope everyone is
making you feel at home.

417
00:30:18.483 --> 00:30:21.578
Very much so. It's an
honor to finally meet you.

418
00:30:21.653 --> 00:30:23.019
I'm a bit overwhelmed. sorry.

419
00:30:23.155 --> 00:30:24.680
Don't worry. I don't bite.

420
00:30:24.823 --> 00:30:27.122
No. I know.

421
00:30:27.192 --> 00:30:30.788
It's strange. I was supposed
to interview your husband.

422
00:30:31.830 --> 00:30:35.164
It was scheduled for a
few days after he died.

423
00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:38.993
It was going to be an exclusive.
We'd had a number of pre-interviews.

424
00:30:39.071 --> 00:30:40.664
Questions we'd agreed on.

425
00:30:42.007 --> 00:30:43.703
Questions like?

426
00:30:44.910 --> 00:30:49.746
Like. was the President
going to pardon him. and when?

427
00:30:50.549 --> 00:30:53.485
Will you? Even
now. posthumously?

428
00:30:56.288 --> 00:30:58.985
I know you did an exclusive
with <i>The New York Examiner.</i>

429
00:30:59.091 --> 00:31:02.653
but I'm guessing that's only
going to scratch the surface.

430
00:31:03.729 --> 00:31:05.755
I bet you have more to say

431
00:31:05.831 --> 00:31:09.393
- about the state of your marriage.
- Miss... Uh. Cruz. is it?

432
00:31:09.468 --> 00:31:11.061
I don't know if
anyone's told you.

433
00:31:11.203 --> 00:31:13.297
but when the President
visits this part of the plane.

434
00:31:13.372 --> 00:31:14.932
it's usually considered
off the record.

435
00:31:15.707 --> 00:31:17.685
But you can ask my Press
Secretary anything you like.

436
00:31:17.709 --> 00:31:18.909
once we're back on the ground.

437
00:31:29.421 --> 00:31:33.153
You're especially
quiet this evening.

438
00:31:33.225 --> 00:31:34.716
Maybe I'm a little agitated.

439
00:31:39.731 --> 00:31:42.758
Our patients don't do too
well when it comes to fireworks.

440
00:31:44.236 --> 00:31:45.260
Pardon me.

441
00:31:51.977 --> 00:31:53.070
Yes?

442
00:31:53.545 --> 00:31:56.913
I don't understand why you
leave that on when we're meeting.

443
00:31:56.982 --> 00:32:00.783
Well. it's not like you're saying
anything different. or new.

444
00:32:00.852 --> 00:32:03.219
Your dedication to your
script would be admirable.

445
00:32:03.288 --> 00:32:06.417
If it weren't so concerning.

446
00:32:08.560 --> 00:32:14.227
In a few weeks. I'll be appearing at a
hearing regarding your state of mind.

447
00:32:14.299 --> 00:32:16.325
And when it comes
to your confession...

448
00:32:16.802 --> 00:32:20.637
Even a guilty man changes
his story now and then.

449
00:32:23.942 --> 00:32:25.877
Who do you answer to?

450
00:32:26.711 --> 00:32:29.704
I mean. who do you work for?

451
00:32:29.781 --> 00:32:30.908
You.

452
00:32:33.251 --> 00:32:36.415
That's the idea. anyway.

453
00:32:36.488 --> 00:32:38.787
Everybody works for somebody.

454
00:32:44.629 --> 00:32:49.192
I worked for a man
who refused to fail.

455
00:32:49.267 --> 00:32:53.898
I respected that.
I appreciated it.

456
00:32:58.910 --> 00:33:02.176
- I'd be dead without him.
- Why?

457
00:33:13.525 --> 00:33:17.326
I was working as an
aide for a congressman.

458
00:33:17.395 --> 00:33:23.164
He was idealistic and naive.
Had one term written all over him.

459
00:33:23.235 --> 00:33:27.229
But I needed a
job. a place to be.

460
00:33:28.206 --> 00:33:31.301
I was barely
keeping it together.

461
00:33:34.045 --> 00:33:36.981
Francis and I met
at some function.

462
00:33:37.048 --> 00:33:40.246
You know. the
kind you stand up at.

463
00:33:42.654 --> 00:33:47.092
I don't know how he knew. but
I had eight bottles in my trunk.

464
00:33:47.158 --> 00:33:51.653
I got through four that night
when he came to my door.

465
00:33:51.730 --> 00:33:55.565
I don't remember
much. Not clearly.

466
00:33:59.104 --> 00:34:03.405
He took me to his
home. But Claire...

467
00:34:07.178 --> 00:34:10.945
Francis got me dry.

468
00:34:11.016 --> 00:34:14.851
I shook so badly. I
thought I was gonna die.

469
00:34:16.288 --> 00:34:20.726
And then when I finally got
clean. he gave me my first job.

470
00:34:23.194 --> 00:34:25.060
As an aide?

471
00:34:26.998 --> 00:34:29.092
Sort of.

472
00:34:29.167 --> 00:34:32.604
He asked me to go talk to
Congressman Kyle from Iowa.

473
00:34:33.038 --> 00:34:34.301
To what end?

474
00:34:36.174 --> 00:34:38.643
To persuade him.

475
00:34:40.111 --> 00:34:41.909
And I did.

476
00:34:47.619 --> 00:34:50.384
But Claire.

477
00:34:50.455 --> 00:34:54.222
the way she treated him.

478
00:34:54.292 --> 00:34:56.727
in life and in death...

479
00:35:04.669 --> 00:35:08.231
You pay a price when you
work for somebody like him.

480
00:35:08.306 --> 00:35:10.866
Somebody you owe.

481
00:35:18.450 --> 00:35:22.478
Somebody close to me
died in a car accident.

482
00:35:24.289 --> 00:35:27.953
That's how I broke the
terms of my house arrest.

483
00:35:29.494 --> 00:35:31.986
I went to see the
site of her wreck.

484
00:35:33.498 --> 00:35:36.627
It was twisted on
the side of the road.

485
00:35:39.437 --> 00:35:42.430
I just stood there.

486
00:35:42.507 --> 00:35:44.976
An accident?

487
00:35:46.778 --> 00:35:48.940
So they say.

488
00:35:50.649 --> 00:35:53.346
And Zoe Barnes?

489
00:35:55.320 --> 00:35:58.313
I killed her.

490
00:35:58.390 --> 00:35:59.824
For the President?

491
00:36:11.002 --> 00:36:14.734
That's what he used
to do when he won.

492
00:36:16.474 --> 00:36:19.103
What did he leave you with?

493
00:36:27.018 --> 00:36:32.150
Last thing that Francis gave me
was the letter opener from his desk.

494
00:36:33.491 --> 00:36:36.290
I mean. I chose it. but...

495
00:36:39.064 --> 00:36:44.162
But I guess really. the last
thing he gave me was an apology.

496
00:36:44.235 --> 00:36:47.694
I spoke to him
the night he died.

497
00:38:18.630 --> 00:38:21.259
<i>My presidency will not rest.</i>

498
00:38:22.100 --> 00:38:25.935
<i>Nancy has been an inspiration
to me. A tireless warrior.</i>

499
00:38:26.004 --> 00:38:29.736
<i>I promise her and all of you that
I will work on behalf of the rights</i>

500
00:38:29.808 --> 00:38:34.405
<i>and freedoms earned over the
last 241 years of our democracy.</i>

501
00:38:34.479 --> 00:38:36.141
<i>Tyrants come in many forms.</i>

502
00:38:36.281 --> 00:38:37.305
Pathetic.

503
00:38:37.448 --> 00:38:40.151
<i>From the American oligarchs
trying to change the very...</i>

504
00:38:48.960 --> 00:38:51.930
Are you sure you don't want
to take an hour or two to...

505
00:38:51.996 --> 00:38:54.397
Mark. I'm inside
the White House.

506
00:38:54.465 --> 00:38:56.934
There's only two of us in the
Oval. so unless you're packing.

507
00:38:57.001 --> 00:38:58.479
it's literally the
safest place I can be.

508
00:38:58.503 --> 00:39:00.631
Well. I'm not packing.
Madam President.

509
00:39:00.738 --> 00:39:03.708
but no one would fault you
for taking a breath for a minute.

510
00:39:05.610 --> 00:39:07.738
I'm breathing just fine.

511
00:39:08.379 --> 00:39:10.905
Can we keep news
of this contained?

512
00:39:10.982 --> 00:39:12.678
I've taken every
possible step. I think.

513
00:39:12.750 --> 00:39:14.548
So. who is he?

514
00:39:15.286 --> 00:39:18.381
Well. they did
forensics on the route.

515
00:39:18.523 --> 00:39:21.459
Compared notes
with the aerial detail.

516
00:39:21.526 --> 00:39:24.928
Homeland Secretary and
the Bureau were brought in.

517
00:39:24.996 --> 00:39:29.400
He never left the place
he took the shot from.

518
00:39:33.705 --> 00:39:37.870
Can you answer a single
question. directly and simply?

519
00:39:39.377 --> 00:39:41.437
He shot himself in the head

520
00:39:41.512 --> 00:39:46.177
with his own U.S.
military issued handgun.

521
00:39:46.251 --> 00:39:50.586
- And we're sure he's the one?
- Yeah. Pro-militia. Anti-government.

522
00:39:50.655 --> 00:39:53.215
Dishonorably discharged last
year. All the typical markers.

523
00:39:53.291 --> 00:39:57.228
Secret Service is confident.
And the Bureau is investigating.

524
00:40:00.531 --> 00:40:04.434
How did Bill Shepherd get
his hands on my speech?

525
00:40:04.502 --> 00:40:08.906
What? Well. the press
usually gets it hours before.

526
00:40:08.973 --> 00:40:11.772
It wouldn't be that hard
to access a copy. I guess.

527
00:40:14.746 --> 00:40:16.977
I won't be signing that today.

528
00:40:21.519 --> 00:40:24.387
You went there to declare your
independence. and you declared war.

529
00:40:24.455 --> 00:40:25.514
That was a mistake.

530
00:40:25.623 --> 00:40:27.683
No. the mistake was I
didn't hire a Chief of Staff

531
00:40:27.792 --> 00:40:29.136
and things are slipping
through the cracks.

532
00:40:29.160 --> 00:40:30.504
That's where I have
to disagree with you.

533
00:40:30.528 --> 00:40:32.053
We need to keep
this circle small.

534
00:40:33.264 --> 00:40:37.565
You know. Francis
warned me about you.

535
00:40:40.138 --> 00:40:42.801
I assure you. I serve at your
pleasure. Madam President.

536
00:40:43.408 --> 00:40:47.243
You need to stop meeting
in my office without me.

537
00:40:50.081 --> 00:40:51.947
Yes. ma'am.

538
00:41:00.124 --> 00:41:01.615
<i>Secret Service took the lead.</i>

539
00:41:02.093 --> 00:41:03.823
But do you believe the theory?

540
00:41:03.895 --> 00:41:07.832
That it was a disgruntled service
person who took a shot at me?

541
00:41:07.899 --> 00:41:08.992
PID does.

542
00:41:10.668 --> 00:41:13.467
I'm asking what you think.

543
00:41:16.174 --> 00:41:19.167
It depends if it was a
warning. or an actual attempt.

544
00:41:20.445 --> 00:41:21.743
Given the accuracy.

545
00:41:21.813 --> 00:41:23.975
the shooter would have
been informed enough to know

546
00:41:24.048 --> 00:41:28.577
that a .50 caliber round
wouldn't penetrate The Beast.

547
00:41:28.653 --> 00:41:29.893
I think he wanted to scare you.

548
00:41:30.488 --> 00:41:31.922
On behalf of someone.

549
00:41:31.990 --> 00:41:34.550
Lots of people make threats
against sitting Presidents.

550
00:41:34.625 --> 00:41:37.857
I'm starting to believe
Francis was murdered.

551
00:41:42.166 --> 00:41:45.762
Before he died. he aligned himself
with some very powerful people.

552
00:41:45.837 --> 00:41:48.015
And I think they turned on
him and they wanted him dead.

553
00:41:48.039 --> 00:41:50.804
and I think they
want me dead. too.

554
00:41:52.243 --> 00:41:54.610
Do you think that sounds crazy?

555
00:41:55.980 --> 00:41:57.608
No. ma'am.

556
00:41:57.949 --> 00:42:00.180
But I think we need to bring
in Special Agent Bowman...

557
00:42:00.251 --> 00:42:02.550
These people. these
powerful families.

558
00:42:02.620 --> 00:42:06.216
they advocate dismantling
intelligence agencies.

559
00:42:06.424 --> 00:42:09.553
CIA. FBI. Homeland.
You know that. right?

560
00:42:09.627 --> 00:42:11.459
- Ma'am. I...
- We cannot bring

561
00:42:11.529 --> 00:42:14.192
anyone else in at the moment.

562
00:42:15.199 --> 00:42:20.103
I'm relying on you the way
I know my husband could.

563
00:42:20.171 --> 00:42:23.073
So. please see
what you can find.

564
00:42:29.514 --> 00:42:32.348
Is it ever "Nate."
or always "Nathan"?

565
00:42:34.052 --> 00:42:35.052
Nathan.

566
00:42:37.055 --> 00:42:41.720
Like Francis. For me. anyway.

567
00:42:44.896 --> 00:42:47.695
Oh. have you spoken
to Doug Stamper?

568
00:42:50.401 --> 00:42:51.460
No.

569
00:42:53.271 --> 00:42:54.796
I'm so worried about him.

570
00:42:54.872 --> 00:42:59.572
He did things no one in this
White House should be proud of.

571
00:43:22.733 --> 00:43:23.860
Hey. Mom.

572
00:43:23.935 --> 00:43:25.699
<i>How many people
do you have there?</i>

573
00:43:25.770 --> 00:43:30.435
Not many. Nobody
that interesting. anyway.

574
00:43:30.508 --> 00:43:33.603
Her visit to the base.
Independence speech.

575
00:43:33.678 --> 00:43:35.977
<i>even the naughty soldier.
is playing well for her.</i>

576
00:43:36.047 --> 00:43:39.017
Her charmed life persists.

577
00:43:39.083 --> 00:43:40.984
<i>Tell Uncle Bill
we should step up.</i>

578
00:43:41.219 --> 00:43:43.916
I can manage the
narrative. De-charm her.

579
00:43:44.122 --> 00:43:45.351
<i>He won't like that.</i>

580
00:43:45.423 --> 00:43:47.892
He's not going to like any of
it. so. what's the difference?

581
00:43:48.826 --> 00:43:49.919
I don't know.

582
00:43:49.994 --> 00:43:54.193
Mom. just say the word.

583
00:43:54.265 --> 00:43:55.597
Trust me.

584
00:43:55.666 --> 00:43:59.535
Don't do a thing
until I get back to you.

585
00:44:18.689 --> 00:44:20.851
Can't even tell
you're still in D.C.

586
00:44:21.692 --> 00:44:25.857
There are parts of this city
that will always remain a secret.

587
00:44:29.567 --> 00:44:32.012
I don't think I'll be welcome back
in the White House press pool

588
00:44:32.036 --> 00:44:35.495
- anytime soon. FYI.
- Doesn't matter.

589
00:44:37.542 --> 00:44:40.444
She won't speak
to me. An interview?

590
00:44:40.511 --> 00:44:43.413
- Not after...
- She will.

591
00:44:50.721 --> 00:44:53.333
<i>Tonight. for the first
time. he was forthcoming.</i>

592
00:44:53.357 --> 00:44:57.488
- But still saying he's guilty?
<i>- Yeah. as always.</i>

593
00:44:57.562 --> 00:45:00.122
And did he mention
Mister Grayson by name?

594
00:45:00.198 --> 00:45:03.464
<i>No. He was just more distressed.</i>

595
00:45:03.534 --> 00:45:08.905
- So. he's getting worse?
<i>- Or better. he's finally talking.</i>

596
00:45:08.973 --> 00:45:12.808
But the idea of his leaving
the facility anytime soon.

597
00:45:12.877 --> 00:45:16.336
that's still out of the question.
I mean. for his own good.

598
00:45:16.414 --> 00:45:17.939
<i>He's either guilty of the crime.</i>

599
00:45:18.015 --> 00:45:20.678
<i>- or psychotic for admitting to it.</i>
- Madam President.

600
00:45:20.751 --> 00:45:23.778
Miss Shepherd is on
the White House line.

601
00:45:25.590 --> 00:45:28.617
Well. maybe it's time to give
him one of the antipsychotics.

602
00:45:28.693 --> 00:45:33.256
Possibly. But we'd have to
consider his history of addiction.

603
00:45:33.331 --> 00:45:37.268
By the way. in answer to your
question. it was a letter opener.

604
00:45:37.335 --> 00:45:40.464
the last thing that Francis
gave him from his desk.

605
00:45:40.538 --> 00:45:44.441
<i>Keep me posted.
Charles. And. thank you.</i>

606
00:45:44.508 --> 00:45:45.601
Sure.

607
00:45:51.749 --> 00:45:53.775
<i>Are you prepared?</i>

608
00:45:55.786 --> 00:45:57.414
Excuse me?

609
00:45:58.756 --> 00:46:02.056
Don't you remember?
Andover? Our prep school joke.

610
00:46:03.894 --> 00:46:06.227
I'm prepared to fail the test.

611
00:46:08.065 --> 00:46:09.727
Are you all right?

612
00:46:12.136 --> 00:46:16.836
I'm sorry to call so late. I heard
about what happened today.

613
00:46:19.543 --> 00:46:22.342
<i>These things have a
tendency to leak out.</i>

614
00:46:22.413 --> 00:46:24.348
<i>I'm worried about you.</i>

615
00:46:24.415 --> 00:46:26.850
It's bulletproof. The
motorcade glass.

616
00:46:26.917 --> 00:46:31.218
<i>- Did they catch the guy?</i>
- How do you know it's a guy?

617
00:46:32.290 --> 00:46:35.783
It's always a guy. Right?

618
00:46:39.330 --> 00:46:43.825
What was it Bill wanted
adjusted in my speech?

619
00:46:46.103 --> 00:46:47.435
<i>Oh.</i>

620
00:46:47.505 --> 00:46:50.942
<i>Something about freedom.</i>

621
00:46:54.812 --> 00:46:57.805
You're in my thoughts. Claire.

622
00:46:58.249 --> 00:47:00.184
Thank you.

623
00:47:00.251 --> 00:47:02.345
<i>He's still with us.
don't you think?</i>

624
00:47:02.420 --> 00:47:05.549
- Who?
<i>- Frank.</i>

625
00:47:05.623 --> 00:47:10.118
<i>We're so glad we got to spend so
much time with him before he died.</i>

626
00:47:11.195 --> 00:47:15.462
He told us some
fascinating things.

627
00:47:15.533 --> 00:47:17.695
He's been on my mind.

628
00:47:20.504 --> 00:47:24.373
<i>Bill and I finally went down
to Gaffney a few days ago.</i>

629
00:47:26.177 --> 00:47:28.703
<i>to pay our respects.</i>

630
00:49:16.620 --> 00:49:20.489
Claire. I shouldn't
have let them! I'm sorry!

631
00:49:21.192 --> 00:49:22.387
Come on out. now!

632
00:49:28.032 --> 00:49:29.432
Are you still there?

633
00:49:29.500 --> 00:49:31.366
Yes.

634
00:50:04.335 --> 00:50:08.602
I know. You want to know
what really happened to him.

635
00:50:08.672 --> 00:50:11.540
A man like Francis
doesn't just die.

636
00:50:11.609 --> 00:50:15.910
That would be...
What's the word?

637
00:50:15.980 --> 00:50:18.006
"Convenient."
